The Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC) has reiterated its commitment to strengthen cyberspace in its bid to protect telecommunications consumers across the country. The commission decried the activities of hackers and cybercriminals who have been deploying sophisticated systems to dupe Nigerians. The Director, Consumer Affairs Bureau of NCC, Mrs. Felicia Onwuegbuchulam, who spoke at the 53rd edition of consumer town hall meeting, tagged: “Mitigating Effects of Cyber Crime: ‘Roles of Telecom Consumers,” in Oyo town, Oyo said the commission had embarked on various initiatives to fight cybercrimes.   NCC strengthens cyberspace to fight cyber crime, protect telecoms consumers Cyber crime: NCC to establish Internet Industry Code of Practice NCC moves to protect telecoms subscribers from cyber attacks OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY